{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB743", "title": "California Financing Law: lawsuit financiers.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["CaliforniaFinancingLaw", "lawsuitfinanciers"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "The California Financing Law generally regulates the business of finance lenders and brokers and prohibits any person from engaging in those businesses without obtaining a license from the Commissioner of Financial Protection and Innovation. The law also imposes various requirements on licensees who offer or sell commercial loans, as defined.\n\nThis bill would prohibit a person from engaging in the business of lawsuit financing, as defined, without obtaining a license from the commissioner, and would generally regulate the business of lawsuit financiers, as specified. The bill would require a licensee who is a lawsuit financier, as defined, to maintain a surety bond, as prescribed. The bill would include lawsuit financing in the definition of \"commercial loan.\" The bill would make willful violations of the California Financing Law by a licensee who is a lawsuit financier subject to a civil penalty, as specified."}], "other_titles": [{"note": "", "title": "Credit unions."}], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2025-02-18", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 21.", "date": "2025-02-19", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on B.&F.", "date": "2025-03-24", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on B.&F.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "F